sentences: Around age ten he took guitar lessons and his first single, with the Friendship Sextet, was released in 1960, when he was thirteen years old.
Akkerman joined the Thijs van Leer Trio in late 1969 which, as the nascent band Focus, was the pit band for the Dutch theatrical production of Hair (recorded as an album in 1969).
Akkerman joined the Thijs van Leer Trio in late 1969 which, as the nascent band Focus, was the pit band for the Dutch theatrical production of Hair (recorded as an album in 1969).
In 1973 Akkerman was voted Best Guitarist in the World by readers of the UK magazine Melody Maker.
His concept album Eli, recorded with Kaz Lux on vocals, won the Dutch Edison Award for best album in 1976.
In 1985, he reunited Focus with Van Leer for an album and accompanying concert.
The band reunited again in 1990 for the Dutch television program Goud van Oud (Old Gold).
During the 1990s and in the 2000s he continued playing with his own band, and also as a solo musician, accompanied by pre-recorded computer-generated background (Roland synthesizers and Linn drums).

In 1992, he was involved in a serious car accident, but he resumed playing in 1993.

Around age ten he took guitar lessons and his first single, with the Friendship Sextet, was released in 1960, when he was thirteen years old.
Akkerman won a scholarship to study at the Amsterdam Music Lyceum for five years, developing his composition and arranging skills.
In the early 1980s he began to experiment with a guitar synthesizer, as on the album Oil in the Family.
In the late 1990s, after an absence of nearly 20 years, he was persuaded to tour the UK again.
